HEADWORD: High five
<hw>High five</hw>. <sn>1.</sn> <def>See <er>Cinch</er> (the
game).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>a celebratory or mutually
congratulatory gesture between two persons performed by each slapping
the other's raised right hand. Also used as a verb.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

